metadata.name: 5ovrc√© #64
metadata.description:
"The essence of art is hidden within its structure; to understand its nature, one must examine the form it embodies."
Theodor Adorno

Within this collection, I focused on the random, dynamic textures created by the Kufic typographic patterns that I enjoy using. The repetition of textures and their layering creates effects that reveal the beauty of randomness. The structure formed by the consecutive repetitions and layering effects highlights the beauty of randomness. Random and repeated animations are based on patterns that are erased and recreated each time. The movement that pauses within the flow and then erases and recreates each texture results in a unique animation. I feel that I have defined myself as an artist in this field now. I sense that I've reached a correct point stylistically. This will be the final work of this year, and it's a turning point for me that it will exist on-chain.

*Start and stop animation: press ‚ÄòQ‚Äô
*Save image: press 'W' to save the current image as a PNG.

metadata.name: MAGNETIK #196
metadata.description:
The output of MAGNETIK reminds me of what tornadoes do to our cities and buildings, yet I imagine the pieces that are about to break off and fly away to be made of metal foil and they do so because of a magnetic force that is pulling them away from where they belong‚Ä¶‚Ä®‚Ä®This one is also a charity run : ‚Ä®
- 20% of the primary sales will go directly to the Processing Foundation, 

- Remaining 80% will be donated to a group of individuals that raise money to buy computers for less fortunate architecture students in a university in the eastern part of Turkey. Please read the next paragraph for a detailed explanation

- I will decide what to do with the secondary sales later if there will be any.

About the majority (80%) of the donation : I decided that the donations should be done in a double-blind way, the donator does not know who they are donating to, and the receivers of the donation will not know from whom the donation is coming from, hence I will transfer the funds these individuals mentioned to act as a middle-step. I feel like this is a hard thing to provide a solid proof for, so I recommend if you have doubts and/or straight away do not trust me or this process, do not mint. I will only be able to provide proof of transfer of funds to a third-party. I trust the people I am sending the funds to, we have done this before (not to brag or anything) and I know that we are affecting younger people‚Äôs life in a good way. Also, I believe that the funds raised from this project alone will not be enough to buy one decent config. computer by itself, if it were so, I would have done it differently.‚Ä®‚Ä®About MAGNETIK : ‚Ä®
MAGNETIK plays on the idea of distorting and breaking grids by employing an illusion of fake 3D and tries to make the resulting composition look good with rhythm and color harmony.
 
- 21 palettes,
- 2 background modes : lights on / lights off,
- 3 grid types,
- plus some surprise features‚Ä¶

I encourage you to try and see the variations before minting :)‚Ä®‚Ä®2 of the grid types are based on https://gorillasun.de/blog/an-algorithm-for-irregular-grids by Ahmad Moussa ( https://twitter.com/gorillasu ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

gradient formulas are based on https://twitter.com/takawo/status/1505876107492720651?s=20&t=S9aU_oNYyjBieBcEmvUV-g
by Takawo Shunsuke ( https://twitter.com/takawo ) and used with his knowledge and kind permission.

Thank you all in advance and have a good day!

DISCLAIMER : I am not a good coder, I have tried to fix my past mistakes from my earlier projects to make some room for new mistakes :) I am hoping that there isn‚Äôt any huge bugs or anything left so you can enjoy your mint! Please hit me up if you have any concerns after minting and we can discuss a solution.

metadata.name: meios #255
A Bugged Forest #190
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Action; System #8
metadata.description:
Action; system is an experimental study inspired by the work of Fran√ßois Morellet. Morellet was one of the founders of the Groupe de Recherche d'Art Visuel (GRAV), founded in the 60s. His work was often informed by systems, a set of rules that determine the artwork, reducing the artist's subjectivity to a minimum.

This work explores what happens when we let go of the strict rule set. Do we ever fully let go?

-----------------
This work was released for the 2023 fundraising exhibition Cure3, and all of the proceeds and 1% of royalties will go to Parkinson's research funds. You can find more information at https://cure3.co.uk/.

-----------------
Controls
- R: new randomized output (the chances of recovering one of these outputs are very slim, that's what the next control is for)
- E: high-res output
- Double click: fullscreen

While you see the eye of Horus, your artwork is loading.

------------------
Made with p5.js & glsl
License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Pixel Management #1552
metadata.description:
#tezpole has demonstrated to us all the importance of effective Cable Management. Intrigued by this challenge, I've delved deep into the pixels of this issue. üôÇ

Drawing inspiration from Rev Dan Catt‚Äôs 'Tally!' and applying similar principles of Cable Management, I've assembled a fun and free OE project.

This project dynamically evolves with each iteration.Grid is determined by a random value calculated as follows: the lower bound starts at 3 and increases incrementally with every 100 iterations, while the upper bound starts at 4 and increases with every 30 iterations. In practical terms, as the iteration count increases, both the minimum and maximum possible number of cols&rows gradually increase.

3200x3200px
Press [s] for .jpeg | Press [p] for .png
Made with p5.js

Rob Scalera | 2023

objkt.name: Now There's None of You Left #55

metadata.name: Now There's None of You Left #55
metadata.description:
Strands of memory are twisted and entangled with each other, blending in and out with the surrounding fog of chaos. Each strand, like a thread of a tapestry, weaves a narrative of the self that is inseparable from the whole. Walking through a thick confusion, you see a solitary slice of the self in each iteration. 

Created in Cables.gl, "Now There‚Äôs None of You Left" is made from layers of randomly generated transparent shapes and various noise textures that are then distorted with a combination of Perlin and Simplex noise. The distortion is also built up in multiple layers, making the shapes sometimes overlay or coil over each other. All these layers of shapes, textures, noises, and distortions create a complex composition that illustrates distorted memories and eroded mind. The resulting scene can look tranquil, sometimes violent, sometimes almost empty. Strands of memory, tendrils of emotions, all brewing in the broth of forgetfulness. And in the midst of this dense confusion, you pray to find a glimpse of clarity. Are you still you, or are you me?

Controls:

[1] Set resolution to 716 x 1024 (default)

[2] Set resolution to 1433 x 2048

[3] Set resolution to 2688 x 3840

* The presets above are suitable for screen viewing up to 4k screen resolution. To set a custom resolution for printing and other purpose, add &res=[desired resolution] at the end of the URL. It will set the height of the image, and the width will be calculated automatically at 0.7 ratio. For example, to get a resolution of 4911 x 7016px (about the size of A2 paper), add &res=7016 as URL parameter.

[c] Capture a screenshot at rendered resolution in live view

Note:
There might be a very slight difference in the minor details between live view and the preview image rendered by fxhash engine. This discrepancy won't appear when you capture a screenshot using the built-in keyboard shortcut.

metadata.name: Shape of 2 #184
metadata.description:
My second minimalist generative token is about a ‚ÄôShape of 2‚Äô. 
2 vertical sets of fine lines create ONE sculpture. The left versus the right side can be either mirrored, show similar or even oppositional expressions - depending on the generated length of the horizontal lines. A ‚ÄôShape of 2‚Äô might remind one of a classic vase, a river or a sculpture - depending on its body language.
